1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Again, the areas in black are the total area covered which we obtained from the mission,

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:18,000
and the areas in red are the pieces which we missed due to the deletion of the plane change

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
and the day early return.

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:27,000
This little piece down here was a oblique pass which we had planned with the pan camera.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,000
It would have taken place on Rev 72 in order to get photographs of Jacendi,

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
which is an area of particular interest to the geology.

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
So you can see that we did lose some data.

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
On the other hand, we did pick up some data that we would not have gotten,

9
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:54,000
and I think overall the effectiveness of the coverage was about 90% of what we had hoped for pre-mission.

10
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:02,000
I really want to express the thanks of the photo team to the flight planners here

11
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,000
and also to Ken for his operation of the cameras during the mission.

12
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:13,000
I know that it was very confusing to be continually changing the flight plan

13
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:18,000
and Ken probably wondered what the hell we were doing with all these on-offs and so on.

14
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:30,000
But really I think we did a very effective job of recovering almost all of the data that we had planned for the mission.

15
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,000
May I have the next slide, please?

16
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:41,000
This is a diagram showing what the Apollo 15 coverage was like.

17
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
This is the planned coverage for the 16 mission,

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
and in the dotted line is the planned coverage for the 17 mission.

19
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The only reason I show this is to indicate that the areas where we did lose data, unfortunately,

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:03,000
are in the areas that were not covered by 15 and will not be covered by 17,

21
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
so that the losses, although small, were real.

22
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
